nd Rachel Aires and Rosário Silva and Rui Vilela and Susana Afonso'),(448,42,5,'INPROCEEDINGS'),(449,42,6,'Workshop on Linguistic Tools and Resources for Spanish and Portuguese'),(450,42,7,'IBERAMIA 2004'),(451,42,8,'http://alfarrabio.di.uminho.pt/~albie/publications/linguateca.pdf'),(452,42,10,'Linguateca: um centro de recursos distribuído para o processamento computacional da língua portuguesa'),(453,42,24,'Puebla, México'),(454,42,9,' Neste artigo apresentamos uma panorâmica da actividade da Linguateca na criação e disponibilização de recursos e ferramentas para a língua portuguesa. Começamos por uma descrição dos objectivos e pressupostos da Linguateca e uma breve história da sua intervenção, e finalizamos com algumas considerações sobre a melhor forma de prosseguir na organização da área. '),(455,42,12,'147--154'),(456,42,13,'2004'),(457,43,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaabdd88)'),(458,43,19,'1'),(459,43,21,'1'),(460,43,4,'Alberto Simões'),(461,43,5,'ARTICLE'),(462,43,10,'{XML::DT} - Down-Translating XML'),(463,43,13,'2004'),(464,43,23,'The Perl Review'),(465,44,17,'SGML'),(466,44,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaaaed30)'),(467,44,21,'1'),(468,44,4,'J.C. Ramalho and J.G. Rocha and J.J. Almeida and P.R. Henriques'),(469,44,5,'ARTICLE'),(470,44,10,'SGML documents: Where does quality go?'),(471,44,22,'MIT Press'),(472,44,12,'75--90'),(473,44,23,'Markup Languages: theory and practice'),(474,44,13,'1999'),(475,45,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaac4f50)'),(476,45,6,'CISTI-2011'),(477,45,29,'Chaves'),(478,45,10,' Oml: A Scripting Approach For Manipulating Ontologies'),(479,45,4,' Nuno Carvalho and Alberto Simões and J.J. Almeida'),(480,45,5,'INPROCEEDINGS'),(481,45,13,'2011'),(482,46,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaac8c90)'),(483,46,2,'EN'),(484,46,3,'May'),(485,46,4,'José João Almeida and Alberto Simões'),(486,46,5,'INPROCEEDINGS'),(487,46,6,'BUCC2010 -- 3rd Workshop on Building and Using Comparable Corpora, lrec2010'),(488,46,7,'Reinhard Rapp and Pierre Zweigenbaum and Serge Sharoff'),(489,46,10,'Automatic Parallel Corpora and Bilingual Terminology extraction from Parallel WebSites '),(490,46,24,'Valletta, Malta'),(491,46,9,' In our days, the notion, the importance and the significance of parallel corpora is so big that needs no special introduction. Unfortunately, public available parallel corpora is somewhat limited in range. There are big corpora about politics or legislation, about medicine and other specific areas, but we miss corpora for other different areas. Currently there is a huge investment on using the Web as a corpus. This article uncovers GWB, a tool that aims automatic construction of parallel corpora from the web. We defend that it is possible to build high quality terminological corpora in an automatic fashion, just by specifying a sensible Internet domain and using an appropriate set of seed keywords. GWB is a web-spider that works in conjunction with a set of other Open-Source tools, de¿ning a pipeline that includes the documents retrieval from the web, alignment at sentence level and its quality analysis, bilingual dictionaries and terminology extraction and construction of off-line dictionaries. '),(492,46,12,'50--55'),(493,46,13,'2010'),(494,47,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaabdf38)'),(495,47,21,'39'),(496,47,2,'EN'),(497,47,3,'September'),(498,47,4,'Alberto Simões and José João Almeida'),(499,47,5,'ARTICLE'),(500,47,10,'Parallel Corpora based Translation Resources Extraction'),(501,47,9,'This paper describes NATools, a toolkit to process, analyze and extract translation resources from Parallel Corpora. It includes tools like a sentence-aligner, a probabilistic translation dictionaries extractor, word-aligner, a corpus server, a set of tools to query corpora and dictionaries, as well as a set of tools to extract bilingual resources.'),(502,47,23,'Procesamiento del Lenguaje Natural'),(503,47,12,'265--272'),(504,47,13,'2007'),(505,48,17,'compiladores'),(506,48,1,'ARRAY(0x7fbccaa67998)'),(507,48,4,'J.J. Almeida and J.B. Barros'),(508,48,5,'TECHREPORT'),(509,48,10,'Teoria das Ling